NFCT_SELRES.purpose:
NFC-A SEL_RES auto-response settings

RFU43, bits [3:4]    - Reserved for future use. Shall be 0.
PROTOCOL, bits [5:6] - Protocol as defined by the b7:b6 of SEL_RES response in
                       the NFC Forum, NFC Digital Protocol Technical
                       Specification
RFU7, bit [7]        - Reserved for future use. Shall be 0.

NFCT_SENSRES.purpose:
NFC-A SENS_RES auto-response settings

BITFRAMESDD, bits [0:4]  - Bit frame SDD as defined by the b5:b1 of byte 1 in
                           SENS_RES response in the NFC Forum, NFC Digital
                           Protocol Technical Specification; 0 for SDD00000 (SDD
                           pattern 00000), 1 for SDD00001 (SDD pattern 00001), 2
                           for SDD00010 (SDD pattern 00010), 4 for SDD00100 (SDD
                           pattern 00100), 8 for SDD01000 (SDD pattern 01000),
                           16 for SDD10000 (SDD pattern 10000)
RFU5, bit [5]            - Reserved for future use. Shall be 0.
NFCIDSIZE, bits [6:7]    - NFCID1 size. This value is used by the Auto collision
                           resolution engine; 0 for NFCID1Single (NFCID1 size:
                           single (4 bytes)), 1 for NFCID1Double (NFCID1 size:
                           double (7 bytes)), 2 for NFCID1Triple (NFCID1 size:
                           triple (10 bytes))
PLATFCONFIG, bits [8:11] - Tag platform configuration as defined by the b4:b1 of
                           byte 2 in SENS_RES response in the NFC Forum, NFC
                           Digital Protocol Technical Specification
RFU74, bits [12:15]      - Reserved for future use. Shall be 0.

playing that sequence at the rate defined in SEQ<n>REFRESH and/or DECODER.MODE.
Causes PWM generation to start it was not running.

PWM1_TASKS_STOP.purpose:
Stops PWM pulse generation on all channels at the end of current PWM period, and
stops sequence playback

PWM2_COUNTERTOP.purpose:
Value up to which the pulse generator counter counts

COUNTERTOP, bits [0:14] - Value up to which the pulse generator counter counts.
                          This register is ignored when DECODER.MODE=WaveForm
                          and only values from RAM will be used.

PWM2_DECODER.purpose:
Configuration of the decoder

LOAD, bits [0:1] - How a sequence is read from RAM and spread to the compare
                   register; 0 for Common (1st half word (16-bit) used in all
                   PWM channels 0..3), 1 for Grouped (1st half word (16-bit)
                   used in channel 0..1; 2nd word in channel 2..3), 2 for
                   Individual (1st half word (16-bit) in ch.0; 2nd in ch.1; ...;
                   4th in ch.3), 3 for WaveForm (1st half word (16-bit) in ch.0;
                   2nd in ch.1; ...; 4th in COUNTERTOP)
MODE, bit [8]    - Selects source for advancing the active sequence

PWM2_ENABLE.purpose:

ENABLE, bit [0] - Enable or disable PWM module

PWM2_EVENTS_LOOPSDONE.purpose: Concatenated sequences have been played the amount of times defined in LOOP.CNT

PWM2_EVENTS_PWMPERIODEND.purpose: Emitted at the end of each PWM period

PWM2_EVENTS_SEQEND.purpose:
Emitted at end of every sequence <n>, when last value from RAM has been applied
to wave counter

PWM2_EVENTS_SEQSTARTED.purpose: First PWM period started on sequence <n>

PWM2_EVENTS_STOPPED.purpose: Response to STOP task, emitted when PWM pulses are no longer generated

SEQSTARTED0, bit [2]  - Write '1' to Disable interrupt for SEQSTARTED[0] event
SEQSTARTED1, bit [3]  - Write '1' to Disable interrupt for SEQSTARTED[1] event

SEQEND1, bit [5]      - Write '1' to Disable interrupt for SEQEND[1] event

LOOPSDONE, bit [7]    - Write '1' to Disable interrupt for LOOPSDONE event

CONNECT, bit [31] - Connection

WDT_CONFIG.purpose:
Configuration register

SLEEP, bit [0] - Configure the watchdog to either be paused, or kept running,
                 while the CPU is sleeping
HALT, bit [3]  - Configure the watchdog to either be paused, or kept running,
                 while the CPU is halted by the debugger

WDT_CRV.purpose:
Counter reload value

CRV, bits [0:31] - Counter reload value in number of cycles of the 32.768 kHz
                   clock

WDT_INTENCLR.purpose:
Disable interrupt

TIMEOUT, bit [0] - Write '1' to Disable interrupt for TIMEOUT event

WDT_INTENSET.purpose:
Enable interrupt

TIMEOUT, bit [0] - Write '1' to Enable interrupt for TIMEOUT event

WDT_REQSTATUS.purpose:
Request status

RR0, bit [0] - Request status for RR[0] register
RR1, bit [1] - Request status for RR[1] register
RR2, bit [2] - Request status for RR[2] register
RR3, bit [3] - Request status for RR[3] register
RR4, bit [4] - Request status for RR[4] register
RR5, bit [5] - Request status for RR[5] register
RR6, bit [6] - Request status for RR[6] register
RR7, bit [7] - Request status for RR[7] register

WDT_RR.purpose:
Reload request <n>

RR, bits [0:31] - Reload request register; 0x6E524635 for Reload (Value to
                  request a reload of the watchdog timer)

WDT_RREN.purpose:
Enable register for reload request registers

RR0, bit [0] - Enable or disable RR[0] register
RR1, bit [1] - Enable or disable RR[1] register
RR2, bit [2] - Enable or disable RR[2] register
RR3, bit [3] - Enable or disable RR[3] register
RR4, bit [4] - Enable or disable RR[4] register
RR5, bit [5] - Enable or disable RR[5] register
RR6, bit [6] - Enable or disable RR[6] register
RR7, bit [7] - Enable or disable RR[7] register

WDT_RUNSTATUS.purpose:
Run status

RUNSTATUS, bit [0] - Indicates whether or not the watchdog is running
